tspan.tspan: This module contains two identical sample & hold
circuits, designed to produce 'staircase' voltages. The
signal present at the sample input (S) is sampled at a
rate set by the signal at the trigger input (T), and held
at that voltage at the S&H output (O). The exact shape
of the staircase depends on the sort of waveform at the
sample input: NOISE or RANDOM signals produce
random patterns; an LFO produces rising or falling
